entry.def: A trademark is a name or symbol that a company uses on its products and that cannot legally be used by another company.
If you say that something is the trademark of a particular person or place, you mean that it is characteristic of them or typically associated with them.

example.ex: ...the spiky punk hairdo that became his trademark.

example.ex: …the designer bars which have become the new trademark of the city.
